<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-08-06T18:33:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-08-06T18:33:00-05:00" n="249" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d249">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">330/8–653: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Mission at the United
                                    Nations</gloss></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d249fn1">Drafted by
                                    <persName>Paul W. Jones</persName> of the Office of <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> Political and Security Affairs and
                                concurred in by <persName>Paul B. Taylor</persName>, Officer in
                                Charge, General Assembly Affairs; cleared with the Bureau of Near
                                Eastern, South Asian and African Affairs; and signed by Assistant
                                Secretary <persName corresp="#p_MURPHYRD1">Murphy</persName>.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-08-06T19:33:00-04:00">August 6,
                                    1953—7:33 p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>35. Request you approach Turkish Delegation soonest re Turkish candidacy
                            succeed Greece on <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>, following position
                            set forth July 24 letter from Secretary to <persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1">Lodge</persName>.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SMITHWB1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                                </persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>